WorkItem.Description:
The completion list is incorrectly showing pretty much everything and the kitchen sink. It seems like it's showing basically every word in the editor. Try this in the playground:

``` TypeScript
class A {
	static foo: string;
}

var a = new A();
a. //Congratulations, EVERY word in this file is part of the completion list
```

One item to note in particular is that static members are appearing in the completion list of instance variables.
